HEADWORD: Junction box
<hw>Junc"tion box</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>A box through which the
main conductors of a system of electric distribution pass, and where
connection is made with branch circuits.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Juncture</ent>⟦br⟧
